This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of brain tumors from magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) data. Additionally, the use of a directed 3D graph and polynomial time s-t cut algorithm suggests that this paper may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of seed points to improve the segmentation results also suggests that this paper may be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of MRI data for medical imaging purposes suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
